@463  = ~Hah! And so we shall both die whilst our guard is down, but at least we shall do so with a smile upon our faces!~
@464  = ~(Your fingers lace comfortably with his, and he flashes you a soft, thoughtful smile. You walk in comfortable companionship for several minutes before he lifts your hand to press a kiss against your palm.)~
@465  = ~(One minute you're enjoying the weight of his hand curled around your fingers, and the next you feel yourself spun into a tight embrace. Haer'Dalis dips you backward, weapons, gear and all, and brushes a warm but faint kiss across your lips. With his eyes half lidded and his silver-blue hair falling about your face in tickling waves, he smiles as he drinks in your expression.)~
@466  = ~'Tis no simple matter to catch the child of a god unawares. Glad I am to have managed such a feat and lived to tell about it.~
@467  = ~(Apparently lost in his own thoughts, Haer'Dalis doesn't acknowledge your touch at first. After a moment, he stops and takes your hand in both of his, eyes focused on his task as he flexes your wrist and digs his thumbs deep into the muscles of your palm. The slow, hard massage radiates outward to each of your fingers in turn, twisting and soothing with expert touches.)~
@468  = ~(When he finishes, he finally glances at you with his dark, unreadable eyes. A smile graces one corner of his mouth before he reaches for your other hand to repeat the treatment.)~
@469  = ~(A chaste but lingering kiss pressed to your lips concludes his spontaneous pampering.)~
@470  = ~(His sidelong glance is warm and teasing.)~
@471  = ~Is my raven feeling a bit needy to<DAYNIGHT>?~
@472  = ~(Haer'Dalis says nothing, but silently accepts your weight against him. Occasionally his fingers trace along the edge of your arm in an absent gesture.)~
@473  = ~Are you unwell? This humble bard believes you sleep far too little for your own good.~
@474  = ~Aye, I believe a good, long sleep is in order for the both of us, my raven. Death will surely catch us up in a blink should we drag ourselves onward for much farther.~
@475  = ~(Sighing, the bard rests against you as well, creating a balanced counterweight that allows the both of you a moment of reprieve, however brief it may be.)~
@476  = ~(He seems to misinterpret the approaching sway of your body as your way of asking for more personal space. He moves away just as you begin to tilt sideways, and you're forced to stagger inelegantly to catch yourself. Haer'Dalis doesn't seem to have noticed.)~
@477  = ~(How it happens, neither of you seem to know for certain, but through some twist of poor luck, you both end up sprawled on the ground. Rubbing his knee, the bard gives a pained shake of his head and helps you up.)~
@478  = ~Between the two of us, there seems to be one too many left feet, aye?~
@479  = ~No, wait...~
@480  = ~(The tiefling turns you gently toward him and pulls you into a full embrace. He sighs against your hair and his hands tighten against your back.)~
@481  = ~This... this I prefer, dear raven.~
@482  = ~Mayhap I should simply carry you, aye, little one?~
@483  = ~Here, my tiny raven, this will be better for the both of us, methinks.~
@484  = ~(He sits down and indicates that you should sit behind him with your back against his. The two of you lean against each other for a peaceful moment.)~
@485  = ~(Haer'Dalis just happens to twist and shift at exactly the wrong moment. It's too late to catch yourself any other way, and you're forced to grab a double handful of the bard's rear to save your nose from being smashed painfully against his back.)~
@486  = ~(Though he startles in surprise at the sudden invasion of his personal space, the Doomguard is soon laughing merrily as he pieces together what has led to your spontaneous groping. His dark eyes sparkle with teasing amusement.)~
@487  = ~All you had to do was ask, dearest raven.~
@488  = ~(Haer'Dalis says nothing, but silently accepts your weight against him. His fingers lace together with yours, his thumb leaving warm trails across the back of your hand, and you feel a ghost of a kiss grace your temple.)~
@489  = ~You look weary, my dear. This humble bard believes you sleep far too little for your own good. Perhaps that is partly my fault, aye?~
@490  = ~(The tiefling turns you gently toward him and pulls you against his chest. He sighs into your hair and lets his hands knead up and down your back in a slow, sensual embrace.)~
@491  = ~Your arms are a comfort to me. I admit, I am a bit mystified how that came to be.~
@492  = ~(He sits down and abruptly pulls you into his lap, curling himself around your smaller body for one peaceful moment of rest.)~
@493  = ~(Though he begins hunting for the source of your discomfort with impassive professionalism, the bard's voice is decidedly teasing when he starts musing aloud.)~
@494  = ~Careful, raven. Invite me to touch you often enough, and I might begin to believe that you are doing it for no other reason than to feel my hands upon you.~
@495  = ~(sigh) I cannot believe these words will pass through my lips, but your pack is an even worse disaster than my own!~
@496  = ~Hmm... I see nothing, <CHARNAME>. Mayhap this mystery pain is trapped beneath your garments? You should check when next we rest.~
@497  = ~Let us take a look a--~
@498  = ~Ah. Ahem. My raven. Do *not* move.~
@499  = ~(Out of the corner of your eye, you see the bard draw one of his swords and turn the point toward your left shoulder.)~
@500  = ~(Remain still.)~
@501  = ~What in the Nine Hells are you doing?!~
@502  = ~(Lurch away from his blade.)~
@503  = ~(Everything is very still and silent for a heartbeat, then you feel the pressure of the tip of his blade against your back and hear a sickening crunch before the weight pulls away.)~
@504  = ~(The bard looses an explosive sigh and tilts the sword for you to see. Impaled upon the point is a beetle the size of your hand, its thick, spiked legs flailing helplessly as it works its dangerous pincers in a vain attempt to free itself.)~
@505  = ~You made a friend, <CHARNAME>.~
@506  = ~Trust me.~
@507  = ~No! Wait!~
@508  = ~(Something claws on needle-like feet up your neck and has almost burrowed its way into your hair before you manage to dislodge it. A beetle the size of your hand scrambles away on spiked legs, leaving you staring after your unwanted passenger.)~
@509  = ~Hmph. You should have trusted me, my hound.~
@510  = ~(He whistles to himself as he searches under your pack, then the bard suddenly goes very silent and still. A heartbeat later, you feel a tug against your pack, and the tiefling moves into your sight, his face somber as he regards the splintered arrow he has pulled free.)~
@511  = ~My raven... You ought not turn your back to archers in the future, aye?~
@512  = ~What a curious coincidence, for I too feel something sharp attempting to dig a hole in my spine. Come, let us sit together a moment and sort out our collection of trinkets and rubbish.~
@513  = ~(The bard hums thoughtfully as he fishes around in the space between your spine and your pack. His fingers playfully poke your ribs from time to time, searching for a reaction, but after a moment he withdraws a small twig and tosses it aside.)~
@514  = ~'Twas naught but some jealous tree's attempt to bring you pain. Shall we go return to the road?~
@515  = ~Forgive me, my raven, but I think you are more than capable of handling the matter yourself, aye?~
@516  = ~Why do I suspect you desire little more than to bring me to my knees on your whim, tiny raven? If 'tis truly a bother, I suggest you remove your pack and conduct your own search.~
@517  = ~(Haer'Dalis crouches down behind you to ease the weight of your pack to the ground. He slides one palm down your back, checking for the source of your discomfort, then begins to examine your pack. After a moment, he sighs and shrugs.)~
@518  = ~I can find nothing, little one. Mayhap it shifted when the pack dropped?~
@519  = ~If you long for my hands upon your skin, my dear, all you need do is say so. Games are unnecessary.~
@520  = ~Hmm... I see nothing, <CHARNAME>. Mayhap this mystery pain is trapped beneath your garments? You should ask this sparrow to give a more thorough inspection when next we rest.~
@521  = ~Whatever would you do without me here to search you for pests, <CHARNAME>?~
@522  = ~Hmph. I thought trust was well established between us, but I see I was wrong, my hound.~
@523  = ~My raven... I will guard your back, but you must be more careful.~
@524  = ~(The bard hums thoughtfully as he fishes around in the space between your spine and your pack. His fingers stroke and linger along your ribs and low across your back, his breath warm and constant against your neck as he stands closer than is strictly necessary for the task. Eventually he withdraws a small twig and tosses it aside.)~
@525  = ~'Twas naught but some jealous tree's attempt to bring you pain. Should I perhaps continue my search, in case there are more villains lingering?~
@526  = ~(Haer'Dalis eagerly complies with your request - by embracing you from the front, his arms beneath yours to pull you snugly against the hard planes of his body. His hands slide beneath your pack, supposedly searching for the source of your discomfort, but with his open mouth pressed to your neck, whispering soft nonsense against your sensitive flesh, it's difficult to say if any progress is being made.)~
@527  = ~I can find nothing, little one, and I suspect you knew I would find exactly that. Mayhap a kiss is in order to encourage your poor bard to trust you once again?~
@528  = ~(Haer'Dalis tilts his head obligingly when your fingers brush aside his hair to peruse the assortment of gold and silver hoops adorning his right ear. He lets out a soft murmur as your fingers move against his unusually hot skin, a curious playfulness in his sidelong glance before he pulls away and shakes his hair back into place.)~
@529  = ~(The tiefling is staring off vacantly into the middle distance when you innocently raise your hand to jingle his earrings. Haer'Dalis startles in a moment of uncharacteristic nervousness, catching one of the rings roughly on your outstretched fingers, and he recoils with a hiss of pain between his teeth.)~
@530  = ~Give fair warning when next you feel the need to abuse this poor sparrow, aye raven?~
@531  = ~(Your finger brushes delicately down the row of shining rings, a faint, musical chime reaching your ears as they bounce against each other. Haer'Dalis smiles at the sound.)~
@532  = ~And now you will think me less mad when I say I ever hear music in my head, my raven.~
@533  = ~Do you like my decorations, fair friend?~
@534  = ~I do. They suit you.~
@535  = ~I wish I had some pretty hoops like that for my ears.~
@536  = ~They're a bit impractical.~
@537  = ~There's too many of them. They look silly.~
@538  = ~I've always hated earrings.~
@539  = ~Thank you, <CHARNAME>.~
@540  = ~Aye, they would suit you well.~
@541  = ~I cannot argue with that. I once had a cambion grab hold of them and tear the whole lot straight out of my ears! I was most grateful for healing magic that day, I can assure you.~
@542  = ~Oh, but a male must adorn himself with more shiny baubles than the next male if he wishes to attract the attentions of lovely females. Even the simplest of birds knows this, my raven.~
@543  = ~'Tis a good thing you have little need for them then, aye?~
@544  = ~Oh! Easy, my hound. I believe that last battle nearly saw me less an ear, and 'tis still tender.~
@545  = ~Your affection is always desired, but not always wise. You may play with me another time, my raven, but let us focus on other things for the moment.~
@546  = ~If you are attempting to count them, let me know the number, aye? I do believe more than one have fallen victim to your enemies.~
@547  = ~Careful, my raven. Your frail Doomguard's ears are rather sensitive, and your touch is... alarmingly distracting.~
@548  = ~(Haer'Dalis preens a bit at your attention, and his eyes follow you long after you've moved away.)~
@549  = ~(The bard replies your advance with one of his own. His open palm hovers just above your skin as his thumb traces a long trail from the tip of your chin, along the line of your jaw, then finally up the curve of your ear. His fingers curl lightly in your hair before he winks slyly and pulls away.)~
@550  = ~(The tiefling's mane of silver-blue locks sifts between your fingers like spun silk, the hair lustrous and thick enough to make even a modest woman jealous. Something about the way he glances at you makes makes it clear that he is proudly aware of the envy he inspires.)~
@551  = ~(The bard sighs with dramatic sadness as you curl a strand of his hair around your finger.)~
@552  = ~'Twas once much darker, my raven, when this sparrow was young and foolish. It seems to become more silver by the year. Wisdom and reason tell me 'tis part of the natural decay of all life, but vanity insists otherwise.~
@553  = ~(Haer'Dalis makes a soft hum of pleasure as your fingers feather through his long locks, but the sound is cut short by a grimace of pain when you accidentally catch one of the decorative braids with a sharp tug.)~
@554  = ~The worst pain is the one we welcome willingly, aye?~
@555  = ~Think you this sparrow a kitten, waiting eagerly for you to stroke him at your whim?~
@556  = ~Enjoying this sparrow's plumage, are you? If it interests you so, keep an eye out for anything that might be nesting in there, aye? I would not be surprised, considering the places we often choose to rest our heads. Put your curiosity to good use, hmm?~
@557  = ~(You lift one of the beaded locks woven into the bard's hair, studying the intricate details of both the braid and the carved objects threaded into the hair.)~
@558  = ~They are reminders, my raven, of memories I never hope to forget. That particular memory has been with me for a number of decades, though my sister would cut off your hand for daring to touch it. Women are strange in that way, wouldn't you agree?~
@559  = ~(Haer'Dalis watches with interest while you weave a lock of his hair into a tiny braid. He regards you with open surprise, then a sudden contemplative tenderness softens his face briefly before he shakes off his bemusement and gestures for you to walk ahead of him.)~
@560  = ~Hmm? Was there something in my hair? No, no, answer this poor sparrow not. If 'twas so, I do not want to hear what it was.~
@561  = ~Mmm... if you but call for a rest, I would gladly lay my head in your lap and give you leave to do this for the rest of the <DAYNIGHT>.~
@562  = ~(The tiefling draws in a sharp breath as your fingertips thread through his hair, nails catching against his scalp. The gaze he turns upon you is heavy and thick with sudden, unexpected desire. He closes any distance between you in an instant, his hands now in your hair, cradling the back of your head and tilting your mouth to hover but a hairsbreadth from his parted lips.)~
@563  = ~(You can feel the indecision in his touch.)~
@564  = ~Temptress...~
@565  = ~(He releases you and turns sharply away.)~
@566  = ~I am well enough, my raven. Longing for The Cage at times, but worry not for this sparrow.~
@567  = ~Anxious, my raven, anxious for battle! 'Tis no shortage of violence in your fair presence, but this poor bard's appetites are oft insatiable.~
@568  = ~There is a stone in my boot, a buckle of my bracer has snapped clean in two, something in my pack is digging into my spine, and I have an insufferable tune spinning circles 'round my mind. All in all, I am as well as can be expected, raven.~
@569  = ~I fare well, for my thoughts are filled with you. Strange, is it not?~
@570  = ~Hmm... why *is* a raven like a writing desk...? Could it be that... Oh, apologies my dear raven, but my mind is lost within itself. Let us speak some other time.~
@571  = ~Splendid am I, my raven. The beautiful sky overhead, blood on my blades, a powerful woman beside me, food in my belly, death waiting around the corner and music in my heart! What more could a Doomguard ask for?~
@572  = ~Dead on my feet is what I be, my hound. Let us to rest, lest this tiefling make his bed on this very ground!~
@573  = ~Bruised and battered, but worse have I seen. I shall live to see another battle, have no doubt of that, my raven.~
@574  = ~My wounds pain me greatly, my relentless hound. If you wish to see me a grave man, let us press onward; if you wish for me to fight by your side for another day, I must seek healing immediately.~
@575  = ~Weary, worn and battle sore, my raven. Let us have rest! This actor cannot keep his mask in these circumstances, and I shall surely terrify you with my true face!~
@576  = ~Aye? A bit of rhyme I heard long ago has run circles 'round my mind this last hour. 'Tis one verse I devote to you, my raven.~
@577  = ~For one brief moment, let me see into your mind
Let me wander through your past to see what I might find
Let me dive into the darkest recesses of your heart
Help me understand you, down to your deepest part~
@578  = ~But will you, I wonder? Aye, I wonder indeed.~
@579  = ~For you, my raven.~
@580  = ~In her darkest hour
She refuses to cower
She screams to the night
'Not without a fight!'~
@581  = ~When all seems lost
And not worth the cost
She throws back her head
'I am not yet dead!'~
@582  = ~Shadows lurking behind
The night tempts her mind
She cries, wild and free
'You cannot have me!'~
@583  = ~In her worst nightmare
She will never show fear
But scream to the night
'Not without a fight!'~
@584  = ~Fate cruel and menacing
When nothing would stop us
You lashed your arrows to prey
Upon our own foolishness~
@585  = ~Insecurity tipped that so poisoned the mind
I lash out at you Fate and your bolts of despair
Sent with such venom to keep us apart
To deny us true love and the embrace we desired~
@586  = ~But you oh Love! Do not try and hide
You trickster you are not innocent in this
Blood is on your hands with your elusive techniques
To enrapture complete, then perform such torture~
@587  = ~As you dangle us, your victims upon the rack
Stretching us past the point of tolerance
I look upon lovers in the mist, specters all
In the tragedy of epic love abounding~
@588  = ~Cruel you two Vixens are
How I hate your very names
I would dash your heads upon the rocks
But in my misery I am weakened~
@589  = ~In my rapture I cannot see past her
I am powerless to defeat you here
Fate and Love who gave you the power
To perform such vindictive miracles~
@590  = ~The world was ours! Life was only a step away
With one kiss as the fairy tales portray
We would have succumbed to you Love
With one moment, our life would have paid you tribute~
@591  = ~But cruel Fate and elusive Love
You denied us our ransom and stole our fancy
Paralyzed our young minds with curare
Brought our false fears to bear with your shots~
@592  = ~How I hate you Fate! How you pain me Love!
I forsake you both! I challenge you to meet me
For battle awaits you, your doom awaits!
I shall shame you. Even to the shame of my house~
@593  = ~As I stand here with only shield in hand
String your vicious bows, aim them foolishly for my destruction
Launch your barbs, line your sights with my heart
But your poisons cannot touch what is not there~
@594  = ~For my heart is sent away from me
Freely given to roam the Stars above
I challenge you Fate! I decry you Love!
For I have found what you sought to deny~
@595  = ~Alas, this sparrow is of a different mind altogether at present. Perhaps another time, my raven.~
@596  = ~I recall a dark but lovely verse I once learned from a Prime. 'Twas a man scorned by love, or so he claimed. This sparrow saw him in the arms of a different lover every other night, so 'tis possible his sincerity was lacking.~
@597  = ~Oh Love, oh miserable Love
Who spurned you so?
To make your gifts seem so unattainable
Should they only be imagined in old tales
And the dreams of fairies in the fields?~
@598  = ~My diamond, so much like the sun
Life-giving, yet so far out of reach
May the internal fires of the sun
Burn through me and leave me not
A once burned shell, blessed with no beating heart~
@599  = ~Oh how glorious to be consumed by the sun
To have your flesh dyed red, for all to see!
Oh I miss you so when the rains come
My whole body aches for you once again
'When,' I cry, 'will you foul clouds run away!'~
@600  = ~How my mind laughs at the plight of us mortals
With one life to live, and one soul to give
All our days should be spent under the sunshine's rays
But quiver not again, the clouds will soon depart
As the day no longer lingers, bracing for deep nights~
@601  = ~Oh Love, oh miserable Love!
Who spurned you so?
To make our efforts seem for naught
No! I refuse your libations to defeat
I call forth my destiny, to one day be free~
@602  = ~It cannot be described
It can never be named
It is not confined
And never ashamed~
@603  = ~It can be beautiful
It can be terrible
It can be wonderful
Or completely unbearable~
@604  = ~Perfect it is not
And yet it is wise
It can never be bought
Or won as a prize~
@605  = ~It has more strength in one
Than a thousand men
It cannot be undone
Nor can it condemn~
@606  = ~I often wonder what these silly poets think as they build impossible expectations upon ephemeral emotion. Ah, but 'tis not this sparrow's place to judge the artist for their art, I suppose.~
@607  = ~I once found a scrap of parchment crumpled in the hand of a dead courtesan. Never you mind why this poor sparrow was searching her body to begin with, but scratched upon this paper were several sad verses that have lingered in my mind ever since.~
@608  = ~No matter what I do
I can't seem to get ahead
When I think I'm moving forward
I find I'm falling back instead~
@609  = ~I struggle and I strive
To make things work out right
But when I look around me
My dreams are nowhere in sight~
@610  = ~I carry this exhaustion
Reaching to my very core
I'm trying to keep going
But my everything feels sore~
@611  = ~I keep fighting so hard
To keep my hope alive
I'm stricken with despair
As I struggle and I strive~
@612  = ~Alas that I am shackled by sure gravity
Drawn to the heavens, but held to earth
Down in the dust of this pale, dry crust
If only I could hold the stars at night
And be consumed by their infinite light~
@613  = ~Absorbed by the expanse of the spans of stars
Released into the eternal light of the sun
Never in my dreams would I have dared
To feel the piercing malaise of my heart
I feared the stars when I was young, but never will I again~
@614  = ~(The bard catches your hands and raises each of them to his lips one at a time, his nearly black eyes sparkling as if in amusement, but his expression is solemn as he watches your face.)~
@615  = ~Your sun will set and yet will rise again
In between the moon's gentle changing phases
Like your heart's steady, gentle rhythm
Rides upon my breast like a golden locket
I have come to believe in your destiny
To ride upon the waves of your embrace 
Sailing to nowhere and everywhere at once~
@616  = ~To hold you against me closely
Your flesh intertwined with mine
Oh how my heart cries out for more
As I wait upon desires and my dreams
To be with you in each fragile living moment
Or hear your voice whispering upon my ears
And holding your hands, feeling each heart beat
As our passion collides and bursts forth anew~
@617  = ~(Haer'Dalis gives you a heavy, lingering gaze that starts at your feet and caresses its way up your body to eventually stop at your eyes.) Though short has been my stay on the Prime thus far, I begin to appreciate its scenes and scenery more with each passing day.~
@618  = ~The rain comes oh so sudden on this scene
So softly falling, lightly glazing
The green, green grass of spring
As the water pools in mountains soon be spilling
Building, building, gathering such speed
Flowing, flowing as the river always rushing
But slowly down the walls does the water fall
The raindrops plunge and merge together 
With the clear blue waters
As the river flows, flows, flows~
@619  = ~The river slowly graceful 
Holding tightly to the canyon walls
Feeling 'round each bend and curve
Touching every rock and crevice
Caressing every rock and crevice
Merging swiftly merging
Eroding slowly along the canyon
It continues building, building
The water swiftly meeting, greeting
As the river flows, flows, flows~
@620  = ~The river quickly shifting, 
Ever flowing, rougher going
As the rapids do approach
The water dashes, splashes, dashes,
With fierce white foam, its interactions
Grasping, grasping every rock and crevice
The tension escapes, as water imparts
Harmoniously overtaking the limits of the canyon wall
Rushing, rushing, splashing at the canyon walls,
As the river flows, flows, flows~
@621  = ~Then the rapids ending, ending 
Calmly slowing with smooth trails upon the river
The water silky, now so silky, rubbing
Along the canyon walls, slowly
Ever slowly, the water gently caressing
Along every rock and crevice
Lightly scratching every rock and crevice
As it slowly marches toward the deep
The river flowing, flowing out to now calm seas
But the river will be always flowing, ever flowing~
@622  = ~Aye, my raven? Ah, do my marks bother you?~
@623  = ~No, I just find them curious. They look like scars.~
@624  = ~On the contrary, I find them quite alluring.~
@625  = ~They're so strange.~
@626  = ~My father, tortured man that he was, flew into a rage one night and took his fury out on my young face with a carving knife. I can still hear my sister's screams, feel the hot blood pouring down my neck as I struggled...~
@627  = ~Hah! My raven, you should see your face. 'Twas nothing so traumatic, I assure you. I was born with these marks, perhaps a gift of my mother's heritage. They are no more painful than freckles, I imagine.~
@628  = ~(Your naked fingertips explore the intricate marks on the bard's face. They appear to be scars at first glance, the flesh smooth and glassy like poorly healed burns, but the symmetry and flawlessness of the lines suggests some other origin.)~
@629  = ~(After a moment of indulging your explorations, Haer'Dalis traps one of your hands and gently bites your fingertip, an amused smile on his lips.)~
@630  = ~(The bard murmurs appreciatively under your attentions, tilting his head back to allow you to stroke the smooth lines adorned on his chin. With his eyes half-lidded and a sleepy smile on his lips, he looks much like a cat enjoying a good scratching.)~
@631  = ~Ah, uh, my raven, as much as I adore your attentions, 'tis quite difficult to watch for danger with your hands fluttering about my face so.~
@632  = ~(Haer'Dalis seems amused by your interest, and allows you to poke and prod his face for several moments before he laughs lightly and pulls away from you.)~
@633  = ~(The tiefling pulls away when you reach for him, flashing you an inscrutable glance before he turns to hide his face from your sight.)~
@634  = ~(Haer'Dalis is frowning and appears lost in thought when you raise your hand to stroke his face. His reaction is a sharp intake of breath, a flinch and a lurching step away from you, leaving you standing with your hand hanging in the air while he stares at you with something very much like fear in his eyes.)~
@635  = ~(One blink of those dark pools, and the emotion is gone, replaced by awkward amusement and a sheepish laugh.)~
@636  = ~My imagination was run away with me, my raven. Forgive my ridiculous antics.~
@637  = ~(As you idly trace the patterns, Haer'Dalis raises his hand and trails his fingers across your cheeks and chin, drawing an imaginary mirror image of his markings on your flesh. His smile is warm and perhaps a little wistful.)~
@638  = ~Ah, my raven, that tickles!~
@639  = ~(sigh) Must you poke and prod me like a slave at market?~
@640  = ~(The kiss begins innocently enough, just a simple brush of your lips against his, but you both lean in for more, over and over, deepening the contact with every kiss until your display borders on obscene. Breathing raggedly, Haer'Dalis pulls away and runs his fingers through his long hair, now tousled by your affection.)~
@641  = ~My raven, you are a burden upon my self-control. A burden I do not mind in the least.~
@642  = ~Let us abstain from such pleasures for the moment, my raven. You would not wish me to lose my head for a kiss, would you?~
@643  = ~My dear raven, you taste like mystery and destiny. An addictive combination.~
@644  = ~Mmm... as delightful as this is, we must not linger overlong lest out enemies catch us unawares.~
@645  = ~(You lean in to give the tiefling a kiss on the cheek, but he turns his head suddenly to catch your mouth with his. A hum of pleasure rises in his throat as he pulls you into a fierce embrace, his tongue teasing your lips for only a moment before he pulls away. He tilts his head and smiles, a promise shining in his dark eyes.)~
@646  = ~(The bard cradles your face in his hands and kisses you lightly on your forehead, your cheeks, the tip of your nose, and finally, lingeringly on your lips. He is smiling as he gestures for you to walk ahead of him.)~
@647  = ~Come, my lovely raven, let us be off lest I forget why we are here to begin with.~
@648  = ~(Just as you turn to him, Haer'Dalis also turns toward you, catching both of your hands in his. Carefully, as if you are fragile or delicate, the bard raises each of your hands to his lips and lightly kisses your palms. Twining your fingers together, he pulls you close and ghosts a kiss against your forehead, his breath leading a warm trail down between your eyes and the length of your nose until his lips finally caress yours.)~
@649  = ~(When the moment ends, he says nothing as you draw apart, but he keeps one of your hands tucked into his grasp for several more minutes.)~
@650  = ~(Haer'Dalis picks you fully up off the ground, his arms tucked securely around your waist, and kisses you lightly on your forehead, your cheeks, the tip of your nose, and finally, lingeringly on your lips. He is smiling as he settles you back on the ground.)~
@651  = ~Come, my tiny raven, let us be off lest I forget why we are here to begin with.~
@652  = ~(Though he is not a tall man by human standards, Haer'Dalis is tall enough compared to you that unannounced kisses are impossible when he's standing up. Fortunately, he is crouched on his haunches to adjust his pack, providing you a rare opportunity.)~
@653  = ~(His attention stays fixed on the task at hand as you approach, and a tiny upward twitch at the corner of his mouth is the only warning you get before he grabs your shoulders and uses his own body weight to rock backward, dragging you unceremoniously into his lap. Nimble fingers caress the back of your neck as he plunders your mouth with a quick, ravening kiss. His breath is hot and heavy against your lips when he releases you.)~
@654  = ~There are so many things I wish to do to you right now, my little tease, even here in the dirt for all eyes to see.~
@655  = ~Not to complain, but if you intend to seek my lips often, perhaps I should walk on my knees so I have no need to bend to your whim so often.~
@656  = ~(Haer'Dalis sighs, leaning into your embrace.)~
@657  = ~I am a creature who thrives off of complexities, off of confusion and argument and mystery, and yet the simplicity of being in your arms undoes me every time.~
@658  = ~Forgive me, my affectionate raven, but I do not wish to let my guard down. Later, you have my word.~
@659  = ~As pleasing as it is to be the object of your desires, I would much prefer we save such displays for times when we carry less leather and metal on our persons. 'Tis not nearly as erotic as some might think, aye?~
@660  = ~Are you certain your mother was not a succubus? I have known many in my life, but none made me lose my focus the way you do.~
@661  = ~(The bard seems distracted and barely returns your embrace with more than minimal pressure. When you pull away, however, he gently kisses the corner of your mouth and places your hand in the bend of his elbow, offering you a wan smile as you set out arm in arm.)~
@662  = ~(The tiefling catches you around the waist and spins with you in his arms, sweeping you up in an amorous display of affection. He presses his lips against the side of your throat, murmuring something too quiet for you to hear, but the vibration of his mouth sends chills over your skin.)~
@663  = ~(He releases you after a moment with a sigh and a smile.)~
@664  = ~(The moment you reach for him, Haer'Dalis turns and takes a step closer to you, his shoulder colliding with yours and knocking you both off balance. You try to catch yourselves and each other at the same time but only succeed in sending the tangled pair of you crashing to the ground, the tiefling squashed beneath you.)~
@665  = ~(He groans, then lets out a pained laugh, dark eyes sparkling even as he grimaces and tries to sort out the mess that is your limbs, armor, clothing and weapons.)~
@666  = ~If you wanted me on the ground this instant, all you had to do was ask, my hound. Save me the bruises, aye?~
@667  = ~(You start to wrap your arms around the tiefling's waist, but he grasps your hands and drops to his knees instead. Unbothered by the filthy ground beneath him, he places your arms around his neck before embracing you, his palms warm against the small of your back.)~
@668  = ~You are a powerful creature indeed, that you can bring this Doomguard to his knees for little more than the promise of your warm embrace.~
@669  = ~Mmm... oof!~
@670  = ~Oh, dear one, we shall have to carry about a stool for you to stand on for moments like this. Bending to your desires is a terrible burden on this poor sparrow's back!~
@671  = ~(The tiefling loops his arms around your waist and lifts you easily off the ground, sweeping you up in an amorous display of affection. He presses his lips against the side of your throat, murmuring something too quiet for you to hear, but the vibration of his mouth sends chills over your skin.)~
@672  = ~(He sets you gently onto the ground after a moment with a sigh and a smile.)~
@673  = ~(The tiefling graciously accepts your attentions by slipping his hand around the back of your neck to mirror your actions. For a long, lazy moment, the two of your do nothing more than enjoy the feel of one another.)~
@674  = ~(The bard's rumbling groan of appreciation is surely lascivious enough to draw stares, but he seems far too busy enjoying the feel of your hand on his skin to care what anyone else - including you - might think of him.)~
@675  = ~No, not here. Save your touch for another time.~
@676  = ~(The bard cringes and gingerly moves away from you.)~
@677  = ~I am grateful for your touch, my dear, but I fear my flesh is far too tender at present. When next I feel it wise to take a blow in your stead, do be kind enough to remind me of this moment, aye?~
@678  = ~(Haer'Dalis happens to turn suddenly just as you reach for him, and your hand catches him squarely in the throat. A choked sound escapes him, and though he recovers himself quickly enough, the look he casts you is equal parts exasperation and amusement.)~
@679  = ~Oh, you are temptation made flesh, fairest one, but let us save such intimacies for places that afford us greater privacy.~
@680  = ~(His chin drops hard against his chest as the tension drains from the line of his shoulders under your ministrations. Soft words of appreciation slip between his lips in whispered snippets, and when you withdraw, he gifts you with a contented smile.)~
@681  = ~(He chuckles softly and sweeps you up in a warm embrace.)~
@682  = ~Seeing you poised on the tips of your toes just so, straining to reach this sparrow's plumage... Ah, you are far too adorable and wonderful for your own good, darling <CHARNAME>.~
@683  = ~(The bard seems to read your mind and kneels before you just as you reach to touch him. He holds your gaze as you run your fingers over his heated skin, honest affection shining in the dark pools of his eyes. Taking your free hand in his, he lifts your palm to his lips and brushes faint, tickling kisses across your palm and the tips of your fingers.)~
@684  = ~A pity we cannot linger, my sweet <CHARNAME>. Thank you for this.~
@685  = ~(Haer'Dalis clearly did not notice your approach. Just as you reach up to touch him, he moves your direction, colliding rather painfully with you in a clatter of gear and weapons. His hand whips out to steady you, but the both of you stumble to your knees in a messy and painful tangle.)~
@686  = ~Ah... raven... we have to stop meeting like this, aye?~
@687  = ~'Twould be my pleasure, fairest raven.~
@688  = ~Are you certain that is what you want? Do not think me reluctant, but give the question some thought. Intimate interludes are not the same as prolonged companionship, and I would wish you to know your mind before you dive in, as it were.~
@689  = ~(He moves in very close to you, but does not touch you. His eyes burn with naked longing.)~
@690  = ~If that is your desire, know that you will not wake rested the next day should I have anything to say about it.~
@691  = ~(A warm, lingering kiss seems to be the only answer he is willing to provide.)~
@692  = ~My raven, at most times I am more than content to be used by you. But in this? No, I fear this I cannot do. Not even for you.~
@693  = ~My raven...~
@694  = ~(He shakes his head sadly, his eyes guarded.)~
@695  = ~That would be most unwise.~
@696  = ~And... you think your lover will not notice this new arrangement? Is he, perhaps, blind, deaf and dull-witted?~
@697  = ~I have little interest in being butchered in my sleep by your jealous lover, my hound. I shall have to decline.~
@698  = ~(Haer'Dalis walks beside you, silent and thoughtful, but his dark eyes stray your direction frequently.)~
@699  = ~(The tiefling appears to be lost in his own thoughts.)~
@700  = ~What turns your attention my way, raven? Are you well?~
@701  = ~I just needed to reassure myself that you're still here.~
@702  = ~(sigh)~
@703  = ~You look tired, Haer'Dalis.~
@704  = ~I need your touch.~
@705  = ~There is nowhere I would rather be.~
@706  = ~Until the moment entropy catches me up, I am yours, my raven.~
@707  = ~If I should ever willfully leave your side, know that I would not do so in secret. I am here, <CHARNAME>.~
@708  = ~(He lifts your hand to his lips and brushes a kiss across your knuckles, but his expression is troubled and his touch is brief.)~
@709  = ~(He echoes your sigh, then flashes you a grim smile.)~
@710  = ~If there were ever a time to drink ourselves into a blind stupor, this would be it, aye?~
@711  = ~(The tiefling's arms pull you close and cradle you firmly against his chest. Leaning into the embrace, he seems to be drawing comfort from your presence.)~
@712  = ~Rest has not come easily for any of us, methinks. This too shall pass, aye?~
@713  = ~As do you, though I think perhaps the theft of your soul is a good excuse for looking less than perfect.~
@714  = ~Worry not. 'Tis nothing that cannot be cured.~
@715  = ~(His fingers capture yours tightly and he presses a kiss against the crown of your head.)~
@716  = ~'Tis something I gladly provide.~
@717  = ~(His hesitation is noticeable, and even when he finally moves toward you, his only action is to brush your cheek with his knuckles. His dark eyes are well guarded, and it's difficult to imagine what he might be thinking.)~
@718  = ~My feelings reflect yours, but we must not let down our guard.~
@719  = ~(The tiefling catches your gaze and holds it for a long moment, his impossibly dark eyes revealing no hint of emotion. As he turns his gaze away from you, his brow furrows in deep thought.)~
@720  = ~(Haer'Dalis hums a slow, sorrowful tune under his breath. His faraway expression reflections the emotions of the melody.)~
@721  = ~If you've a need, name it and I shall see it done.~
@722  = ~You are a wonder to me, my raven. I cannot comprehend where you find your smile each morning.~
@723  = ~(The bard's answering smile lacks its usual enthusiasm.)~
@724  = ~(Haer'Dalis nods once and looks away.)~
@725  = ~(Haer'Dalis responds with a wondering shake of his head.)~
@726  = ~Oh, how chaos clings to you. 'Tis your second shadow.~
@727  = ~Your attention always flatters me, but mayhap we ought focus on more important matters at present.~
@728  = ~This humble sparrow only hopes your smile is not a mask for your true feelings, my hound.~
@729  = ~(Your hand slides easily into his grasp, but he moves your hand to the bend of his elbow instead, pulling you close so that your hip brushes against his with every other step.)~
@730  = ~Your touch is a welcome distraction, my raven.~
@731  = ~(The bard curls his fingers around yours, caressing your knuckles with his thumb. Even when necessity forces you to move apart, he seems reluctant to let go.)~
@732  = ~(At the touch of your hand, the bard stops and turns toward you, his eyes searching your face carefully. Whatever it is he sees there seems to reassure him, and he offers you a slight smile before twining his fingers with yours.)~
@733  = ~(Your fingers lace comfortably with his, and he flashes you a soft smile. You walk in comfortable companionship for longer than is probably wise.)~
@734  = ~(Startled, the tiefling jerks away from your hand, only to let out an explosive sigh when he realizes it was only you.)~
@735  = ~Apologies, my raven. It seems that all this crawling through dungeons has taken its toll on my nerves.~
@736  = ~(He glances down at your conjoined hands, then turns a sincere and thoughtful look toward you.)~
@737  = ~Thank you, my raven, for allowing this humble bard to participate in the grand play that is your life.~
@738  = ~(The tiefling turns you gently toward him and pulls you against his chest. He sighs into your hair and lets his hands caress your back in a slow, soothing embrace.)~
@739  = ~(He does not speak, but the warmth of his arms around you says more than a thousand words.)~
@740  = ~(Haer'Dalis casts you a regretful glance and shakes his head.)~
@741  = ~Let us not delay, my raven. Not now.~
@742  = ~(Haer'Dalis tilts his head obligingly when your fingers brush aside his hair to peruse the assortment of gold and silver hoops adorning his right ear. He lets out a soft murmur as your fingers move against his unusually hot skin, and he offers you a warm sidelong glance before he pulls away and shakes his hair back into place.)~
@743  = ~(Haer'Dalis turns away when you reach for him, though it's difficult to say if he is ignoring you or if he simply did not notice you.)~
@744  = ~This sparrow has certainly seen better days, but then so has my raven, aye? Such is the price of this life we lead at times.~
@745  = ~Spare no worry for me, raven. You've enough to weigh you down already.~
@746  = ~We are all of us scarred and worn and pieced back together, are we not?~
@747  = ~I do not know. (sigh) And I do not know *why* I do not know, or if I should worry that I do not know.~
@748  = ~(Haer'Dalis catches your hand and holds it against his cheek for a long moment. His eyes are mysteriously void of emotion, but his fingers tremble against yours.)~
@749  = ~(After a moment of indulging your explorations, Haer'Dalis traps one of your hands and kisses the tip of your finger.)~
@750  = ~(One blink of those dark pools, and the emotion is gone, replaced by uncharacteristic embarrassment and the faintest hint of shame.)~
@751  = ~(As you idly trace the patterns, Haer'Dalis raises his hand and trails his fingers across your cheeks and chin, drawing an imaginary mirror image of his markings on your flesh. His attention wavers and he stares in open wonderment at your bottom lip before physically shaking off his bemusement.)~
@752  = ~There will be time for such things later perhaps, my hound.~
@753  = ~(Though his touch is brief and hesitant, Haer'Dalis spends a long moment gazing into your eyes after you part. It looks as though he is searching for something.)~
@754  = ~(The bard seems distracted and barely returns your embrace with more than minimal pressure.)~
@755  = ~Save your strength, my raven. These trials are not yet at an end.~
@756  = ~(His hesitation is obvious, and you watch a war of emotions flicker behind his eyes.)~
@757  = ~My raven... I am here for you. Whatever you need of me, I shall provide if I am able.~
@758  = ~Indeed? Is something the matter, my raven?~
@759  = ~No, forget I said anything.~
@760  = ~I think you have the wrong idea about us. I just want us to be friends.~
@761  = ~It's about Anomen...~
@762  = ~It's about Gavin...~
@763  = ~It's about Edwin...~
@764  = ~It's about Kelsey...~
@765  = ~It's about Tsujatha...~
@766  = ~It's about Angelo...~
@767  = ~It's about Solaufein...~
@768  = ~It's about Kivan...~
@769  = ~It's about Xan...~
@770  = ~It's about Keldorn...~
@771  = ~It's about Aran...~
@772  = ~It's about Valygar...~
@773  = ~It's about Lask...~
@774  = ~I am disappointed, but I understand. I wish you every happiness the realms have to offer, dear raven.~
@775  = ~Alas, I shall miss the warmth of your skin against mine, but all things must have an end. I wish you every happiness the realms have to offer, dear raven.~
@776  = ~The valiant and hypocritical defender of your virtue? Aye, what of the hound?~
@777  = ~It was nothing. Never mind.~
@778  = ~I thought you should know that there's nothing going on between the two of us. I'm just not interested in him.~
@779  = ~I think I might be attracted to him.~
@780  = ~If, hypothetically, I was perhaps interested in pursuing Anomen... what would that mean for you and I?~
@781  = ~Whatever is developing between the two of us, I thought you should know that I'm not serious about him.~
@782  = ~This relationship I have with Anomen, I think it might be getting serious.~
@783  = ~I'm not sure how you'll react to this, but would you perhaps consider helping me make him jealous?~
@784  = ~I know it might seem like I'm committed to him, but it's not as serious as it might seem.~
@785  = ~Things have become pretty heavy between Anomen and myself.~
@786  = ~He's neglected me a bit lately. Will you help me make him jealous?~
@787  = ~Whatever spark might have been between the two of us is dead. It's over.~
@788  = ~Anomen and I are no more than friends now, but I want him back so badly! Help me win him back, Haer'Dalis!~
@789  = ~Indeed? I do not understand the appeal personally, but mayhap you see in him what I cannot.~
@790  = ~Beyond this sparrow questioning your taste in men?~
@791  = ~Mayhap he is aware of this? Anomen is not the sort to take such matters lightly, or make attachments with casual intent.~
@792  = ~Indeed, and no doubt he would agree. He is not the sort to take such dalliances lightly.~
@793  = ~Surely you realize that would put this sparrow at no small measure of risk, aye? Make no mistake, I do not fear the hound, but such tactics have a history of spectacular misfires.~
@794  = ~His is a heart of light and kindness, aye? 'Tis perhaps a bit too bright for this sparrow. What of him, my raven?~
