@852  = ~Kivan and I are no more than friends now, but I want him back so badly! Help me win him back, Haer'Dalis!~
@853  = ~I cannot question his beauty or his intrigue, but I must question the wisdom of pursuing a man such as he. Let your heart be sure, my hound, or let it feel naught at all.~
@854  = ~Then you be a cruel hound indeed.~
@855  = ~I will not insult you with doubt, but I do find it difficult to believe.~
@856  = ~I think mayhap such tactics will not work on all men, my raven.~
@857  = ~A most amusing berk, is he not? Much like this sparrow, and yet so very, very *not*. What of him, raven?~
@858  = ~If, hypothetically, I was perhaps interested in pursuing Xan... what would that mean for you and I?~
@859  = ~This relationship I have with Xan, I think it might be getting serious.~
@860  = ~Things have become pretty heavy between Xan and myself.~
@861  = ~Xan and I are no more than friends now, but I want him back so badly! Help me win him back, Haer'Dalis!~
